  "page": "Battle at Long Lake",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table style=\"margin: 4px 10%; border: 1px solid #aaa; background:#fbfbfb;\"><tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px 0 2px 0.5em;border-left: 10px solid #1e90ff;\">\n<div style=\"width: 50px;\"><img alt=\"Mbox notice.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/40px-Mbox_notice.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/60px-Mbox_notice.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/80px-Mbox_notice.png 2x\" />\n</div></td><td style=\"border: none; padding: 0.25em 0.9em; width: 100%;\"> <b>Note:</b> The title of this article is conjecture and may be subject to change.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background: #B0C4DE; text-align:center;\">Battle at Long Lake</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Date</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_226_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">226&#160;AC</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Place</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Long_Lake\" title=\"Long Lake\">Long Lake</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">north</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Result</th><td>\nNorthern victory</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<table style=\"width:100%; text-align:left;\">\n<tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Combatants</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\"><a href=\"/index.php/Free_folk\" title=\"Free folk\">Free folk</a></td>\n    <td width=\"50%\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Stark.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Stark.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/7/7e/House_Stark.svg/30px-House_Stark.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"33\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/7/7e/House_Stark.svg/45px-House_Stark.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/7/7e/House_Stark.svg/60px-House_Stark.svg.png 2x\" /></a> The <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">north</a>, led by <a href=\"/index.php/House_Stark\" title=\"House Stark\">House Stark</a>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Umber\" title=\"House Umber\">House Umber</a></li></ul></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Commanders</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\">King <a href=\"/index.php/Raymun_Redbeard\" title=\"Raymun Redbeard\">Raymun Redbeard</a>†<br /><a href=\"/index.php/Red_Raven_(free_folk)\" title=\"Red Raven (free folk)\">Red Raven</a></td>\n    <td width=\"50%\">                                      Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Willam_Stark\" title=\"Willam Stark\">Willam Stark</a>†<br /><a href=\"/index.php/Artos_Stark\" title=\"Artos Stark\">Artos Stark</a><br />Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Harmond_Umber\" title=\"Harmond Umber\">Harmond Umber</a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Strength</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\">Thousands<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_wall_and_beyond:_the_wildlings.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_wall_and_beyond:_the_wildlings.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td>\n    <td width=\"50%\">                                      Unknown</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Casualties</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\">Significant<br /><a href=\"/index.php/Raymun_Redbeard\" title=\"Raymun Redbeard\">Raymun Redbeard</a>†<br />Raymun's sons†</td>\n    <td width=\"50%\">                                      Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Willam_Stark\" title=\"Willam Stark\">Willam Stark</a>†</td></tr>\n</tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>A <b>battle at Long Lake</b> was fought between <a href=\"/index.php/Free_folk\" title=\"Free folk\">free folk</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">northern</a> forces of Houses <a href=\"/index.php/House_Stark\" title=\"House Stark\">Stark</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/House_Umber\" title=\"House Umber\">Umber</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_226_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">226&#160;AC</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Prelude\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Prelude</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Battle\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Battle</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Aftermath\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Aftermath</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Prelude\">Prelude</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Battle_at_Long_Lake&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Prelude\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Beyond_the_Wall\" title=\"Beyond the Wall\">Beyond the Wall</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Raymun_Redbeard\" title=\"Raymun Redbeard\">Raymun Redbeard</a> united the <a href=\"/index.php/Free_folk\" title=\"Free folk\">free folk</a> and took the title of <a href=\"/index.php/King-Beyond-the-Wall\" title=\"King-Beyond-the-Wall\">King-Beyond-the-Wall</a>. The <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a>, whose guard was down, let Raymun's reavers get atop the <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a> and throw down ladders for the army waiting beneath. The army of wildlings attacked south of the Wall, causing Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Willam_Stark\" title=\"Willam Stark\">Willam Stark</a> to leave <a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">Winterfell</a> and march north, calling Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Harmond_Umber\" title=\"Harmond Umber\">Harmond Umber</a>'s banners too.<sup id=\"cite_ref-RPG_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-RPG-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Battle\">Battle</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Battle_at_Long_Lake&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Battle\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Lords Willam and Harmond met Raymun on the shores of <a href=\"/index.php/Long_Lake\" title=\"Long Lake\">Long Lake</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">north</a>, with the free folk forced to fight with the lake at their back.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_wall_and_beyond:_the_wildlings.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_wall_and_beyond:_the_wildlings.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Although Raymun beheaded Willam, he was in turn slain by Willam's younger brother, <a href=\"/index.php/Artos_Stark\" title=\"Artos Stark\">Artos the Implacable</a>, and the wildling force was defeated.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-RPG_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-RPG-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The sons of Raymun Redbeard were also killed, but his younger brother, <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Raven_(free_folk)\" title=\"Red Raven (free folk)\">Red Raven</a>, fled back <a href=\"/index.php/Beyond_the_Wall\" title=\"Beyond the Wall\">beyond the Wall</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd69.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd69.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Aftermath\">Aftermath</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Battle_at_Long_Lake&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Aftermath\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Artos_Stark.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/c/cc/Artos_Stark.png/300px-Artos_Stark.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/c/cc/Artos_Stark.png/450px-Artos_Stark.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/cc/Artos_Stark.png/600px-Artos_Stark.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Artos_Stark.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Artos_Stark\" title=\"Artos Stark\">Artos Stark</a> and the head of <a href=\"/index.php/Raymun_Redbeard\" title=\"Raymun Redbeard\">Raymun Redbeard</a></div></div></div>\n<p>The Night's Watch arrived too late to join the battle. Artos ordered them to dispose of the dead. The <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Commander_of_the_Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Lord Commander of the Night&#39;s Watch\">Lord Commander of the Night's Watch</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Jack_Musgood\" title=\"Jack Musgood\">Jack Musgood</a>, was known as Sleepy Jack afterwards.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-RPG_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-RPG-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Raymun's invasion was the last major wildling threat until the rise of <a href=\"/index.php/Mance_Rayder\" title=\"Mance Rayder\">Mance Rayder</a>, which coincided with the <a href=\"/index.php/War_of_the_Five_Kings\" title=\"War of the Five Kings\">War of the Five Kings</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Battle_at_Long_Lake&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_wall_and_beyond:_the_wildlings.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_wall_and_beyond:_the_wildlings.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_wall_and_beyond:_the_wildlings.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Wall and Beyond: The Wildlings.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-RPG-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-RPG_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-RPG_2-1\">2.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-RPG_2-2\">2.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones_(game)\" title=\"A Game of Thrones (game)\">A Game of Thrones RPG and Resource Book</a>, Guardians of Order</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">3.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\">3.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_7\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 7\">Chapter 7</a>, Jon II.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd69.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd69.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_69\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 69\">Chapter 69</a>, Jon XIII.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403122421\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.120 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.473 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 608/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 9623/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 10282/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 1449/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 11/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 2803/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.240/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 5.43 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  427.411      1 -total\n 94.31%  403.083      1 Template:Battlebox\n 94.05%  401.976      1 Template:Infobox\n  4.27%   18.230      5 Template:Ref\n  3.29%   14.051      2 Te